Ext.data.JsonP['Create_an_Organization']({"guide":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?>\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n    <title>Create an Organization</title>\n\n    <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n    <meta content=\"Scroll EclipseHelp Exporter\" name=\"generator\">\n\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" media=\"print\">\n</link></link></link></meta></meta></head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <div class=\"header\"/>\n\n        <div id=\"src-50168160\" class=\"content\">\n                        <h1>Create an Organization</h1>\n    <p>    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox admonition admonition-warning aui-message problem shadowed information-macro\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Enterprise Subscription Required!</div>\n            <p>This AMPLIFY Appcelerator Services feature requires an Enterprise Subscription.    </p>\n    </div>\n        <p>If you are an administrator of your organization, you can create child organizations under your parent organization. Child organizations share the user and device resources with the parent organization and cannot be allotted more than what the parent has not used.    </p>\n    <p>If your organization is an authorized AMPLIFY Appcelerator Services Reseller and you are an admin user, you can create two kinds of organization:    </p>\n<ul class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>Internal organizations, called <strong class=\" \">Groups</strong>, are the same as children organizations that will use your parent organization&apos;s allotted user and device resources.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>External organizations, called <strong class=\" \">Customers</strong>, is a group that has purchased the AMPLIFY Appcelerator Services, which is allotted its own pool of user and device resources.    </p>\n</li></ul>    <p>To create an organization:    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>Log in to <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"https://platform.appcelerator.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Dashboard</a>.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Click on the <strong class=\" \">Orgs</strong> or <strong class=\" \">Profile</strong> menu and select <strong class=\" \">Manage Organizations</strong>.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>On the <strong class=\" \">Manage Org</strong> tab, click <strong class=\" \">New Organization</strong> in the upper-right.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">Name</strong> textfield, enter the name of the organization.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">Admin Email</strong> textfield, enter the email address of the person who will be administrating the organization.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">Dashboard Users</strong> field enter the number of seats to allocate for Dashboard users in the new organization.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">Test Devices</strong> field enter the number of devices allowed to use Appcelerator Test services.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>To invite users to the new organization, click <strong class=\" \">Invite Members to this Organization. </strong><br><strong class=\" \">    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/50168160/invite_users_new_org.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/50168160/invite_users_new_org.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">\n </img></strong><br><strong class=\" \">Note: </strong>This button is disabled if the specified number of <strong class=\" \">Dashboard Users</strong> is not greater than 1.    </br></br></p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Click <strong class=\" \">Create Organization</strong>.    </p>\n    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/50168160/new_org.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/50168160/new_org.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" width=\"500\">\n    </img></li></ol>        </div><a id=\"editButton\" href=\"https://wiki.appcelerator.org/pages/editpage.action?pageId=50168160\"><span>Edit</span></a>\n    \n        \n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","title":"Create an Organization"});